    <descriptions>
        <definition>
            <para>A title in non-Latin script Romanized according to the ALA-LC Romanization Tables.</para>
        </definition>
        <customization co="object" dd="p16786coll3">
            <para>Search for Romanized title in &lt;a href="http://catdir.loc.gov/catdir/toc/becites/ladino/63062107a.html"&gt;LOC Ladino catalog.&lt;/a&gt;</para>
            <para>If a potential match is found, confirm that it is the correct title: it may be helpful to review information included in the web display such as the publisher, printer, and publisher/printer locations.</para>
            <para>Copy the Romanized title just as it appears in the LOC record, usually following the period after the author name.</para>
            <para>When copying from LOC, retain this version: do not edit to match the Title-field value.</para>
            <para>If no record exists, Romanize according to the ALA-LC &lt;a href="https://www.loc.gov/catdir/cpso/romanization/ladino.pdf"&gt;Ladino romanization table.&lt;/a&gt;</para>
            <para>When Romanizing a title, only include the portion transcribed in the Title field.</para>
            <para>Required for all compound objects.</para>
        </customization>
        <customization co="no" dd="p16786coll3">
            <!-- Draft instructions for SSDC (dd="p16786coll3") standalones; no standalones expected in coll at this time -->
            <para>Romanize title according to the ALA-LC &lt;a href="https://www.loc.gov/catdir/cpso/romanization/ladino.pdf"&gt;Ladino romanization table.&lt;/a&gt;</para>
            <para>When Romanizing a title, only include the portion transcribed in the Title field.</para>
            <para>Required for all standalone objects.</para>
        </customization>
    </descriptions>
    <examples>
